> 
> If I may be a beginner here: how does "begin ... end" differ from "( ... )"?  
> In practice I've found them to be interchangable, but that could just be an 
> accident.

No accident, they are just the same. It's matter of personal taste to
use one or another. begin ... end is used mainly in imperative contexts.

